{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κῦδος</b>, εος, τό, <br /> <b>glory, renown</b>, especially in war, ὡς ἄν μοι τιμὴν.. καὶ κ. ἄρηαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.84; ἐκ δὲ Διὸς τιμὴ καὶ κ. ὀπηδεῖ 17.251 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; Ἕκτορι κ. ὄπαζεν (i.e. Ἀπόλλων)[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 16.730; ὁπποτέροισι πατὴρ Ζεὺς κ. ὀρέξῃ 5.33 \">Refs</a>]; κ. ἀρέσθαι to win <b>glory</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 12.407 \">Refs</a>], etc.; κύδεϊ γαίων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1.405, 5.906 \">Refs</a>]; of a person, μέγα κ. Ἀχαιῶν <b>glory</b> of the Achaeans, of Odysseus,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 9.673, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.184 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Nestor Epigrammaticus, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.42, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.79 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>].—<i>Epic dialect</i> word, also in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 23.13, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.8.ά, 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 215, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 2.89, +others, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 317 (Lyric poetry), “Pers.” 455 (not in 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus or 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus)\">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; in a mock-heroic line, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 200 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; never in <i>Attic dialect</i> Prose.","strongNumber":"G8117","accentedUnicode":"κῦδος","shortDef":"dignity","mediumDef":"dignity","stepGloss":"dignity","stepTransliteration":"kudos","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}